# Daily memories (Docs/Memories)

- Maintain a **single daily work log file** at `Docs/Memories/DD-MM-YYYY-work.md`.
- On every session end (or before responding when significant work was completed), **append** a new section:
  - `### Session N`
  - **Time**
  - **Goal**
  - **Work completed** (bullets)
  - **Files changed / added** (paths)
  - **Commands run** (if any)
  - **Notes / follow-ups**
- If the daily file doesn’t exist yet, create it using the convention above.
- If the user provides an agent transcript path/uuid, include it as a source link like:
  - `[<short title>](<uuid>)`

# Backup workflow (“BACKUPZ”)

When the user says **exactly** “BACKUPZ” (or clearly requests a backup):

## 1) Record it in today’s memory

- Add a **Commands run** entry noting that a backup was created and include:
  - destination root: `D:\Rudra\MSPL-044\BACKUPS\wan-buffer-website-backup`
  - the created folder name

## 2) Create the backup on disk

- Destination root (Windows): `D:\Rudra\MSPL-044\BACKUPS\wan-buffer-website-backup`
- Create a new folder inside it named:
  - `{DD-MM-YYYY}-backup-{important-title-info}`
  - Example: `09-04-2026-backup-converted-HTML-into-NEXTJS`
- Copy the project **from repo root** into that folder excluding heavy/generated directories:
  - `node_modules`
  - build outputs (at least): `.next`, `dist`, `build`, `out`
  - also exclude common caches: `.turbo`, `.vercel`, `.cache`, `coverage`
- Ensure `Docs/` is included in the backup.

## 3) Implementation detail

- Prefer using the repo script `scripts/take-backup.ps1` to perform the copy so behavior stays consistent.

